# WebRTC TURN (optional but recommended for video/voice across different networks / NAT)
# Use commas to list multiple URLs (UDP + TCP) with the same username/password.
# Railway coturn example (host from the TURN service’s public URL, no https://):
# NEXT_PUBLIC_TURN_URLS=turn:your-coturn.up.railway.app:3478,turn:your-coturn.up.railway.app:3478?transport=tcp
# NEXT_PUBLIC_TURN_USERNAME=same-as-TURN_USERNAME-on-Railway
# NEXT_PUBLIC_TURN_CREDENTIAL=same-as-TURN_PASSWORD-on-Railway
#
# Generic:
# NEXT_PUBLIC_TURN_URLS=turn:relay.example.com:3478,turn:relay.example.com:3478?transport=tcp
# NEXT_PUBLIC_TURN_USERNAME=turn-user
# NEXT_PUBLIC_TURN_CREDENTIAL=turn-secret
